; Dungeon Demo — level 1, static layer (structure and fixtures).
; One character per cell; every row must be the same width.
; Lines starting with ';' and blank lines are ignored.
;
;   #  solid rock          .  floor
;   P  party start         D  dusty floor (air turbidity 1)
;   T  wall torch sconce   F  fire brazier (blocks movement)
;
; Grid glyphs are never lowercase: lines starting with a lowercase letter
; are records. "palette" records declare the level's surface palette by
; CATALOG ID (project catalog/walls.cat, floors.cat, ceilings.cat); the game
; loads only the sets those ids resolve to (each needs its worn block meshes
; baked, see ModelBaker.cpp). "decoration" records are static entities whose
; type is a catalog id (catalog/decorations.cat), e.g.
;   decoration banner 4 2 north
; "fixture <sconce|brazier> <x> <z> [facing]" places a wall sconce or floor
; brazier explicitly (resolved through catalog/fixtures.cat) — unlike the
; one-per-cell 'T'/'F' glyphs, several may share a cell (e.g. two sconces on
; different walls). A sconce facing names the wall it hangs on (must be solid);
; omit it to auto-pick the first solid neighbour. A decoration can take
; "wall=<dir>" to hang flat on that wall (offset to it, facing the room)
; instead of standing at the cell centre — so a sconce, a banner and other
; wall props can all share one square.
; Dynamic content — monsters, items, buttons — lives in level1.ent.

palette wall wall_cobblestone wall_stacked_stone wall_brick_red wall_rock
palette floor floor_cobblestone floor_broken_tile floor_rubble floor_rock
palette ceiling ceiling_stone ceiling_rough
;
; 32x32 layout (4x the old map): a start room (NW) opening onto a great
; pillared hall (N), a dusty fountain hall (centre), a tomb crypt (W), a
; dusty cavern (SW), a treasure vault (S) and gallery/chambers (E/SE), all
; tied together by a looping corridor network. The fountain hall and cavern
; are dust-heavy showcases; the serpent pillar auto-spawns in the NW corner
; of the start room.
